The paper deals with the attribution of cyber-attacks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed argumentation-based reasoner (ABR) is an AI tool that can assist in the analysis of forensic evidence, which makes it relevant to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The ABR also deals with incomplete and conflicting information, which is a common problem in machine learning, making it relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the process of constructing efficient and targeted security measures, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with cyber-attacks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cyber security (cs.CYBER).
